# GitHub PR Target

This checkout has:

- `origin` = `deferredreward/bible-editor-multilingual`
- `upstream` = `unfoldingWord/bible-editor`

The GitHub CLI may resolve bare `gh pr create` / `gh repo view` to upstream because an `upstream` remote exists. For this folder, always pass the repository explicitly when opening or inspecting PRs:

```powershell
gh pr create --repo deferredreward/bible-editor-multilingual --base main
gh pr view --repo deferredreward/bible-editor-multilingual
```

Never accept a PR URL under `github.com/unfoldingWord/bible-editor` for this workspace unless the user explicitly asks to target upstream.
